data.eventDesc: Reversing out of laneway, I couldn't see any traffic behind me, I reversed into the front of another vehicle. There was a truck blocking my view when reversing so I couldn't see the truck. Laneway is usually open both ends as a drive through but today the opposite end had been blocked off.
data.managerComm: I have received correspondence and spoken to the insurer (RAC), they will assess the damage and send through the claim. I agree, the driver either needs to reverse back into the laneway where it is difficult to reverse out from or alternatively, wait until the view is unobstructed so the truck has been moved so they can proceed with full visibility. Correct incident reporting needs to be followed, which includes diagrams and photos of the damage.
